    • Constructor Detail

      • MethodFlow

        public MethodFlow(String methodSig,
                  FlowSource from,
                  FlowSink to,
                  boolean isAlias,
                  boolean typeChecking,
                  boolean cutSubFields)
        Creates a new instance of the MethodFlow class
        Parameters:
        methodSig - The signature of the method containing the flow
        from - The start of the data flow (source)
        to - The end of the data flow (sink)
        isAlias - True if the source and the sink alias, false if this is not the case.
        typeChecking - True if type checking shall be performed before applying this data flow, otherwise false
        cutSubFields - True if no sub fields shall be copied from the source to the sink. If "a.b" is tainted and the source is "a", the field "b" will not appended to the sink if this option is enabled.

      • getCutSubFields

        public boolean getCutSubFields()
        Gets whether sub fields shall not be appended when applying this method flow. If "a.b" is tainted and the source is "a", the field "b" will not appended to the sink if this option is enabled.
        Returns:
        True if sub fields shall be discarded and shall not be appended to the sink
